<%# Cerberus override of Blacklight's "blacklight"-theme Kaminari paginator.
  - Why we override: the upstream paginator (a) never emits the First/Last
    boundary links and (b) honours Blacklight 8's `next_button_position: :before`
    default, which renders "« Previous  Next »  1  2" — Next ahead of the page
    numbers. We want the clearer DRS-v1 order:
        « First   « Previous   1 2 … N   Next »   Last »
    so we render the boundary tags ourselves in a fixed sequence and ignore the
    engine's next_button_position config.
  - Boundary links are OMITTED at the edges rather than greyed out (DRS-v1
    behaviour): on the first page we drop both « First and « Previous, on the
    last page both Next » and Last ». A disabled link that does nothing is just
    noise, so we don't render it at all — the page numbers anchor the position.
  - Available locals: current_page, num_pages, per_page, remote, paginator.
  - Sibling tag partials (_first_page, _prev_page, _page, _gap, _next_page,
    _last_page) are NOT overridden — they fall through to the gem. We restyle
    the .pagination/.page-item/.page-link markup into flat text links in
    app/assets/stylesheets/_pagination.scss.
-%>
<%= paginator.render do -%>
  <ul class="pagination">
    <% unless current_page.first? -%>
      <%= first_page_tag %>
      <%= prev_page_tag %>
    <% end -%>
    <% each_relevant_page do |page| -%>
      <% if page.left_outer? || page.right_outer? || page.inside_window? -%>
        <%= page_tag page %>
      <% elsif !page.was_truncated? -%>
        <%= gap_tag %>
      <% end -%>
    <% end -%>
    <% unless current_page.last? -%>
      <%= next_page_tag %>
      <%= last_page_tag %>
    <% end -%>
  </ul>
<% end -%>
